sourceQuestion:
Suppose you are provided with the following function declaration in the C programming language:
int partition(int a[], int n);
The function treats the first element of a[] as a pivot and rearranges the array so that all elements less than or equal to the pivot are in the left part of the array, and all elements greater than the pivot are in the right part. It then returns the position of the pivot after rearrangement.

The following partially given function in the C programming language is used to find the k^th smallest element in an array a[] of size n using the partition function:
int kth_smallest(int a[], int n, int k) {
    int left_end = partition(a, n);
    if (left_end + 1 == k) {
        return a[left_end];
    }
    if (left_end + 1 > k) {
        return kth_smallest(__________);
    } else {
        return kth_smallest(__________);
    }
}

The missing arguments listed from left to right are respectively:
A. (a, left_end, k) and (a + left_end + 1, n - left_end - 1, k - left_end - 1)
B. (a, left_end, k) and (a + left_end + 1, n - left_end - 1, n - left_end - 1)
C. (a + left_end + 1, n - left_end - 1, k) and (a, left_end, k - left_end - 1)
D. (a + left_end + 1, n - left_end - 1, k) and (a, left_end, k)

